                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I would have handled the tank a little different .... I never stop doing something just because one moron has a problem with it ... too many people think they can run the group by being the loudest rather than the smartest.  Facing a similiar situation myself instead of giving up charm I made certain to charm every add incoming instead of mezzing.  If they pulled 3 then the charmed mob offtanked.  I only got out the mez on pulls with 4 or more.  After every pull I then released the pet with dispel and rooted it letting them tank it down.  The catch:  I didnt charm the add pull I charmed the incoming just to add to the point.  After about 6 times of yelling at me to stop charming the tank gave up.  Moral of the story:  Dont let them push you around in an ldon.... they cant afford to disband you if they want to complete the mission ... and you probably dont want to do another boring ad with them anyway after its over.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
