                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Wow, sounds like some of the LDoNs I have been in...
<br />

<br />
I gave up trying to Charm in groups for just this reason unless there is a nice DC available.  Some players dont get it and its nearly impossible to explain it to them or they have had one bad experience that taints them too much.  Its just too much to try to keep the pet controled and deal with players who want to tell you how to play your character.  Solo, I do pretty well with it (and getting better).  I know lots of you do the "Charm and reCharm as needed" thing, but i tend to charm, use the mob up, going for the kill as the charm runs out and its very low on health, then move on to the next.  I know, bad habit, but it works for me until I can invest some AAs into stronger charms and defensives.
<br />

<br />
Enkidoo</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
