                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally I never charm in a group.  Charming is risky even when you know what you're doing.  Why should I risk myself if I'm not getting solo XP?  I might do so when I get into the higher levels but if anyone in the group has a problem with it then I'll just forget it.  Who cares, I'll still get XP and I can always Gate.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, after all the hasting and mind buffs I typically only have enough mana for mezzing and maybe a few blasts here and there.  I usually don't even bother with making an animation.  Also, depending on where I'm at, I'll tell the puller to pick up two or three things and it's entertaining enough keeping them all mezzed.
<br />

<br />
You shouldn't get too mad at those who are anti-charm.  If you've ever been grouped with someone who wasn't any good at it but insisted on doing so (one time our whole group got wipped out 5 times by an idiot chanter who didn't know how to play his class), you'll understand completely why it raises a red flag with them.
<br />

<br />
But hell ya, even if I was playing my warrior I'd love to have some beastie with us that could quad for 900 dmg</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
