                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">When I play my alts (not so much any more, since I'm pretty much exclusive to my enchanter now), I have a very unusual way of dealing with other enchanters in a group. If we get two or more mobs incoming, I do nothing. Just stand there and wait until the situation has resolved itself.
<br />

<br />
Of course, you sometimes get those enchanters who don't even have an aoe stun up, and run around like a chicken if they get a single resist. Or those enchanters that slow when the mob is, oh, around 30 percent health. Or those enchanters where you get an add, call add ... and 10 seconds later they start reacting.
<br />

<br />
