<br />
Actually, that's another rant.
<br />

<br />
Paladins that can't play their damn class.
<br />

<br />
I mean, for the love of god, Paladins are the best defensive tank out there for xp groups. They can pull at lower levels, have amazing and immediate aggro ability, they can stun *without damage*, they can root, they can heal, they can lay hands, and they can do all this with very low mana spells.
<br />

<br />
So why don't they???
<br />

<br />
I despise paladins that don't stun. I despise even more paladins that stun with their fucking knockback / damage stuns.
<br />

<br />
Cease and Desist. For the love of god, use cease and desist! And at higher levels, use Quellious.
<br />

<br />
In the situation you had Max, all the frickin' paladin had to do was lay an 8 second stun on the mob that was aggroed on you, turn and stun one of the two mobs incoming (or root it for all I care), and they aggro the third and last mob, and call the assist. You would've had everything under control by then, and the 3rd mob would be well on its way to being dead.
<br />

<br />
It's not rocket science, so why do so few paladins do this??? They have ALL the tools to be the best aggro class it the game, and I find it shocking that so many fucking paladins play their class like a gimped warrior who can heal during downtime.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=167673" target="_blank" class="postlink">E65.102/Pr h+ 2.1khp 3.9km ft3 G+ e++ o++ T++ L H++ f- g b- c++++ t+ D-- X-</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
