                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Good paladins are out there, hiding in nooks and crannies.  The other day I was doing a hard with one of my favorite groups leaders (He likes my style, picks me up for the enchanter most of the time, picks up his friends then fills in)
<br />

<br />
 Well. pally shows up to be tank/puller.  I'm slightly nervous but it turns out the guy knows how to root/stun pull.  I had agro maybe once to twice  and it all turned out very well.  He only used dmgless stuns on the mobs if they attacked me or cleric so i could actually mezz them w.o problems.  Mind you.. this pally was guildless, pretty bad equip ect. but he knew exactly what he was doing.  
<br />

<br />
With no pet.. ranger dps ect.. we won it in about 80 min
<br />

<br />
Now on the other hand.. lets talk about shitty clerics.   I did another ldon with him the next day.  We have 2 chanters, she picks up a pet at the very begining, holds it very well.  clerics sends me a tell " Why the **** does she have a pet?"  "Because its very good dps and we will win much faster"  Now later.. this idiot cleric... because he died once, decided "Oh i'm not comin back into the adventure to get my body! i'm not rezzing any of you!  That idiot enchanter pulled 4!"  omfg. The guy said he could handle it.  We asked him at the very begining "You are only a baron, can you handle the heals?"  well.. 20 min into adventure he is saying "I cant heal this fast, we need to pull slower!"  
<br />

<br />
we lost &gt;&lt;  and then my boyfriend trained a spec on him while he was afk and root parked it on him  :finga:</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Clailya Clearmind
